You must teach merging to understand your project. In general, you it means=
 that you should write a .merlin file, that should show merlin where to sea=
rch for your source code, build directory and libraries you=92re using.   I=
t is described [1] at merlin site. Also, you can look at other projects and=
 use them as an example for merlin configuration [2]


[1] https://github.com/the-lambda-church/merlin#merlin-project
[2] https://github.com/BinaryAnalysisPlatform/bap


